---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Fangzhou Jiang" description="A bit more about who I am and what I'm looking for.">
  <div class="about">
    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <section class="section">
      <p>
        I'm Fangzhou, a software engineer based in London, Ontario. My background is in
        backend development and test automation — I've spent years building end-to-end backend
        performance evaluation solutions and test automation infrastructure for large-scale
        distributed systems. I'm now focused on backend engineering and AI, and how the two
        intersect.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How I got here</h2>
      <p>
        I spent 3 years as a Software Engineer in Test at Netease Games in Shanghai. My core
        work centered on backend performance evaluation for large-scale cloud game servers —
        owning the full cycle: designing load test scenarios that reflected real player behavior,
        writing test scripts with a custom Python-based traffic simulation framework, running
        tests at scale against distributed infrastructure — Kubernetes autoscaling, Redis,
        Kafka — simulating up to 2M concurrent users, then collecting and analyzing server-side
        metrics to pinpoint bottlenecks. The findings fed directly into backend optimization
        work, closing the loop between testing and engineering.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond performance testing, I built internal tooling — automated workflows, data
        monitoring pipelines, CI/CD infrastructure, and a workforce efficiency platform —
        and coordinated with global studios across time zones. Shipped on Marvel Rivals,
        Dead by Daylight Mobile, and several other titles.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Western I've been researching AI-driven procedural content generation, which led me
        deeper into the practical side of making LLM systems reliable and production-ready.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
      <p>
        I'm most effective on teams where engineers own problems end-to-end — from design to
        shipping. I prefer working close to the product, not just the infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p>
        The problems I find most interesting: backend systems that need to perform at scale,
        test automation that actually catches real bugs, and building AI features that hold up
        outside of demos.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Outside work</h2>
      <p>
        I build games on the side — mostly Unity projects where I can implement algorithms I
        find interesting (procedural generation, pathfinding, AI behaviour) without the
        pressure of a production codebase.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section contact-section">
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Best way to reach me is email:
        <a href="mailto:fjiang59@uwo.ca">jiangfz1997@gmail.com</a>.
        I'm also on <a href="https://github.com/jiangfz1997" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        and on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/fangzhou-jiang/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .section p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-section p {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
